T1	h1 0 59	For the first time, the brown rust virus “hit” tomato crops
T2	p 60 368	For for the first time in Arcadia the brown wrinkle virus was detected in tomato fruits. The Directorate of Agricultural Economy and Veterinary Medicine of the P.E. immediately made an announcement. Arcadia. According to the announcement, the virus was detected in outdoor tomato crops in the area of Levidi.
T3	b 64 147	for the first time in Arcadia the brown wrinkle virus was detected in tomato fruits
T4	p 369 788	Except tomatoesthe virus also affects plants pepper. It is mainly transmitted mechanically by contact between plants due to cultivation operations such as weeding or fruit collection, as the worker may carry an infected load (plant, seed). Clothing, tools and crates are hotbeds that can carry and transfer the virus to healthy plants, while soil can also carry infected debris capable of multiplying within six months.
