T6	b 414 420	pepper
T7	p 789 1287	Special attention is needed in greenhouses, where the virus can be on the surface of various structures and from there be transferred to the plants. At hydroponic crops there is a risk of the virus entering the water system and from there being transmitted to cultivated plants. Contaminated pollen it can be transferred from plant to plant due to pollinators, while weeds such as stypnus, datula, goosefoot, but also ornamental plants, such as petunia, are places where the brown rust virus grows.
