T11	h2 1288 1296	Symptoms
T12	p 1297 1666	Symptoms vary depending on variety, plant condition and environmental conditions. In tomato crops infected plants have leaves showing chlorosis, mosaic, curling, lamina distortion and occasionally narrowing. The fruits of the plant show yellow-brown rings, brown areas, wrinkling, deformations and uneven ripening, while the plants show reduced flowering and fruit set.
T13	p 1667 1805	Similar symptoms are seen in pepper foliage, with the fruits of the plants showing distortions, uneven color with brown and green streaks.
