T15	p 1813 2094	There are no curative measures for the treatment of tomato brown wrinkle virus (ToBRFV). In order to limit its spread, the following are proposed by the Ministry of Agricultural Development and Food and the Benakeio Phytopathological Institute crop prevention and hygiene measures:
T16	b 1813 1843	There are no curative measures
T17	b 2057 2094	crop prevention and hygiene measures:
T18	ul 2094 3396	 Use of healthy seeds and seedlings, which must necessarily be accompanied by a phytosanitary passport. Intermittent control of plants and removal of those showing symptoms of infection. Frequent disinfection of tools by immersion in a 0.5% NaOCl or Virkon S bleach solution or skimmed milk (at least 3.5% protein content) for at least 15 minutes. Use of disposable shoes, coveralls and gloves by workers performing the various cultivation tasks and changing them between different facilities. Avoiding contact of healthy plants with hands that have been in contact with sick plants (uprooting, tying, pruning, etc.). Existence of carpets with disinfectant at the entrance of the greenhouses. Good washing with disinfectant of all surfaces, trays, etc., inside the greenhouses between transplants / plantings. Use clean or disinfected plastic crates when harvesting the fruit and avoid using them in different facilities. Removal and destruction of all crop residues at the end of the growing season as well as disinfection of the greenhouse areas. Destruction of weeds in the areas around the greenhouse or at a distance of 30 meters around the outdoor crops. Crop rotation for a period of 6 to 12 months with plants that are not affected by the virus, e.g. plants of the gourd family (Cucurbitaceae).
